title.narrative: Emergency Programme Implementation

description.narrative: In Kiunga District of Western Province, 4,717 peoplewere reached with nutrition messages from January to June of 2021. From the total, 2,341 of them were males while the remaining 2,376 were females. Messages were delivered through facility and community outreach in the context of Covid-19. Only13 childrenwere identified with severe acute malnutrition (SAM) and commenced on treatment. Up to 1,347 children had access to all essential nutrition services during COVID-19 in the first half of the year. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:08/01/2022
